    <bioghist>
      <head>Historical Note</head>
      <p>The Union Congregational Church of Bryant, South Dakota, was founded on March 13, 1892,
        with the writing of its first constitution. On March 30th, 1892, the church joined in
        covenant fellowship with Congregational churches in DeSmet, Hetland, Erwin, Lake Preston,
        and Willow Lake. The congregation originally met for worship in the Baptist church and other
        places until a church building was financed and built in 1897. In 1945 a building fund was
        established to remodel the Church, and a basement was later dug and bricked. In 1911, the
        church voted to separate from the Congregational Home Mission Board and become financially
        self-supporting. From 1929 to 1943, the church struggled with both finances and attendance,
        and until 1984 struggled to keep pastors employed. As a result of this, the church shared
        several pastors with the Willow Lake Congregational Church from 1946 to 1987. The church was
        part of the United Church of Christ. In 1993, the Prairie Retreat, a nonprofit led by Rev.
        Marjie Brewton, was sponsored by the church and ran as an extended ministry. The church was
        dissolved in 2020.</p>
    </bioghist>
    <scopecontent>
      <head>Scope and Contents</head>
      <p>The Bryant, S.D. Union Congregational Church records include annual reports, membership
        records, church correspondence, and yearbook reports. Also included are financial records,
        in the form of ledgers, receipts, treasurer's records, and building records.</p>
    </scopecontent>
    <arrangement>
      <head>Arrangement</head>
      <p>The collection has been arranged in chronological order with closely related materials
        grouped together as appropriate.</p>
    </arrangement>
